added.title: The Tiger Train
added.description: When Yong Bao visits Sodor, a jealous Thomas sets out to prove he's the braver train and challenges Yong Bao to a series of bravery challenges, only to have his plan backfire.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Can-Do Submarine Crew
added.description: Thomas and Percy think they're great communicators, but when they're tasked with delivering a submarine to Vicarstown, communication becomes a bit more difficult… to say the least!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Everyone's Best/Stronger Every Day/No More Training Wheels
added.description: When Clementine shows up with a swimming ribbon on her chest, Caillou really wants to have one too./When a new, longer set of monkey bars is installed at the park, Caillou is disappointed./With training wheels on his bike, Caillou is having trouble keeping up with Sarah.

added.title: Caillou the Road Builder/Caillou's Building Adventure/A House in the Sky
added.description: There's been a big storm and the playschool yard is littered with branches./When Daddy and Grandpa help a charity build a new home for a needy family, Caillou comes along./Mommy and Caillou go to visit an old friend of Mom's.

added.title: Caillou Helps Out/Caillou the Firefighter/Caillou to the Rescue
added.description: Rosie is teething and just can't seem to fall asleep./The Fire chief visits Caillou's playschool to teach the children about fire drills./A mischievous Rosie hides Caillou's cars between the cushions on the sofa.

added.title: Caillou and the Big Slide/Caillou the Sailor/Caillou and the Creepy Crawlies
added.description: The playschool is going swimming, and it's Caillou's very first time on a water slide./Mommy and Daddy are going out to a party and Caillou is excited to hear that Grandpa is coming to babysit./Rosie doesn't like bugs - she thinks they're icky!

added.title: Caillou Goes Caroling/A Playschool Party/Caillou's Christmas Eve
added.description: Caillou goes out caroling for the very first time with Mommy, Daddy, Rosie, Grandpa and Grandma./It's a very special day at playschool as they celebrate the many ways of celebrating the holiday season./It's finally Christmas Eve and Caillou just can't wait for nighttime.

added.title: More
added.description: It's bath time! Bing's excited to do the bubbles, but how much bubble goo does Bing need?

added.title: Sparkle Magic
added.description: Sula is the fairy queen and shows Bing her special sparkle magic... will Bing find his own?

added.title: Tree
added.description: Bing and Pando are being diggers, planting trees in the sandpit. What will happen when Pando ruins Bing's digging?

added.title: Where's Flop?
added.description: It's lunchtime! Bing's hungry for carrots. But what happens when Flop pops to the shops and Bing stays at home with Amma and Sula?

added.title: Lunchbox
added.description: It's lunchtime! Bing shows Pando and Sula his brand new Hoppity Voosh lunchbox! And Pando has the exact same one MATCH! But then they mix their lunchboxes up.

added.title: Big Jumping Spider
added.description: Lucas performs epic jumps all around House. Findley is nervous and wishes Lucas wouldn't jump.

added.title: Ghost Camp
added.description: When Lucas and friends go camping, Avocado tells a scary story. Lucas now thinks there's a ghost in the garden.

added.title: What a Stinker
added.description: Chep is very excited: tonight, a rare and extremely stinky plant is going to bloom! But he already promised Mush-Mush to play their favourite game. When he chooses the flower instead, Mush-Mush is angry and the two friends stop talking. But when Mush-Mush realises that Chep is about to miss the blooming, he decides he won't let that happen and helps his friend!

added.title: Return of the Gnomes
added.description: When Gus and Garth's greedy uncle makes his nephews forget the caring, sharing, and generosity they learned from the Care Bears and convinces them to return to their old selfish ways, the Bears must help them remember their caring hearts.

added.title: Compost to Go
added.description: When Mush-Mush, Chep and Lilit take their compost meals back to their home-tree to eat, they think they have made a great new discovery - compost to go! They set up a delivery service so everyone can eat at home too. It's so cool! Except Sushi-Mushi misses hosting everyone at the Food Snail, and everyone starts missing eating together.

added.title: The Light in the Forest
added.description: Cheer bonds with a migrating firefly-like creature, called a Sparklewing, who stows aboard the Cloudseeker. The two become good friends, but there's a problem: Sparklewings must finish their migration to bring life-giving nutrients to the fields of the Silver Lining. Cheer's difficult and emotional parting with her new friend is only possible once they both accept that it's for a greater good.

added.title: What's In the Box?
added.description: Pocoyo's new box takes on a life of its own when Loula accidentally crawls underneath it. Eventually with the help of his friends, Pocoyo works out what's - or WHO'S - in the box.

added.title: Musical Blocks
added.description: Pocoyo and Pato are having great fun playing with some magical blocks which form towers when music is played. But the fun turns to drama when Pato gets stuck on top of a high tower. How can Pocoyo return his ducky friend back to ground safely?

added.title: Paint Me a Picture!
added.description: Pocoyo has decided to paint a portrait. But none of his friends will sit still long enough for him to be able to finish his picture. Pocoyo is sad because he feels like he hasn't managed to do what he set out to do - but looking at his picture with fresh eyes he sees that his picture really does capture the true essence of his friends.

added.title: Elly's Doll
added.description: Pocoyo is charged with looking after Elly's favorite doll, but he breaks it. Instead of telling her the truth, he pretends to be the doll. It's only when nature gets the better of Pocoyo that Elly realizes what's going on. She forgives Pocoyo warmly and mends her doll.

added.title: Wackily Ever After
added.description: Pocoyo and his friends are playing dressing up and the narrator decides to tell a story. The traditional fairy tale takes on a decidedly wacky hue as the characters all undercut the conventions with hilarious and surprising results.

added.title: An UnbeLEAFable Day
added.description: While the trains are setting up for the Vicarstown Fall Festival, Thomas is feeling down about the end of summer and the changing weather.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Dark
added.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

added.title: Stuck
added.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

added.title: Traffic Jam
added.description: Pocoyo is pretending to be a traffic police officer. Aided by a traffic light and a whistle, he is trying to make his friends obey the signs and cross at the crosswalk. This is no easy task, however.

added.title: Pato's Living Room
added.description: Pato's living room has a sofa, a table, a TV and a rug. Pato is settling down to watch television when his friends burst into his house. But Pato does not feel like having company, so he throws them out. In the end, he feels bad for leaving them out and asks them to come back in.

added.title: Cinema
added.description: Pato is going to show a movie for his friends, who will be the audience. He shows us the screen, the seats and the projector. Everything is going well until the film gets jammed and the audience laughs. Pato gets angry but his friends manage to get him to sit down and enjoy the show with them.

removed.title: Blankie
removed.description: It's bedtime and Bing's getting ready for bed. But what will he do when his blankie gets wet in the toilet?

removed.title: Bedtime
removed.description: It's Pocoyo and Pato's bedtime but Pocoyo isn't tired. Every time Pato is just about to fall asleep, he is disturbed by Pocoyo. Eventually Pocoyo is tired out too and together we help Pato drift off to sleep at last.

removed.title: Swimming Pool
removed.description: Bing, Sula and Flop are going to the Swimming Pool, but what will they do when they find that there's no water in the pool?

removed.title: Mush-Mush the Predictor
removed.description: Mush-Mush can't figure out why his sense foot keeps buzzing like crazy until an earthquake shakes the forest. Mush-Mush is sure he predicted it! Convinced he can now predict the future, Mush-Mush starts making predictions for everyone in Mushton.

removed.title: Something for Everyone/Skating Lessons/Caillou Becomes a Waiter/Sticking to It!/New Clothes
removed.description: When the park is closed for the day, Caillou's friends come over to his house to play./When Mom drives Sarah to her skating lesson, Caillou decides he wants to take skating lessons too!/When Mom and Dad are getting ready to go out to a restaurant, Caillou doesn't understand why he can't go too!/When Caillou accidentally breaks one of his toys because his room is a mess, Mom suggests a way to make cleaning up fun./When Caillou dresses himself, he learns it's okay to change from your favorite shorts when you find out it's cold outside.

removed.title: Talkie Taxi
removed.description: Bing and Sula discover a new toy at Amma's creche - Talkie Taxi. What will they do when they discover the taxi talks a lot?

removed.title: Giggle Bug
removed.description: When Pocoyo is down in the dumps, Octopus cheers him up. Elly falls over doing her latest dance routine and Octopus cheers her up too. Finally Pato is in a bad mood, and Octopus has to work really hard to get him to giggle.

removed.title: A Little Something Between Friends
removed.description: Pocoyo and Pato fall out - really fall out. They are so angry with each other that they build a wall between themselves. They each sit sulking on either side of the wall, until gradually they realize that it's no fun being angry with your friend, and actually they miss each other.

removed.title: Did Not! Did Too!
removed.description: Bugs and Lola temporarily decide that they don't want to be friends any longer.

removed.title: The Big Squeak
removed.description: Avocado's new toy is driving everyone crazy with its noisy squeaker.

removed.title: Color My World
removed.description: Pocoyo finds a new toy - a remote control that changes the colors of the things around him. It's great fun until he changes the colors of his friends. We have to help him put things back to the way they were.

removed.title: Pocoyo's Little Friend
removed.description: Pocoyo finds a new little friend - a very hungry caterpillar. He watches with amazement as his new friend transforms.

removed.title: Roller Coasting
removed.description: Thomas wants to show Percy what it's like to ride a roller coaster, so Thomas turns the tracks of Sodor into a thrill ride.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Caillou's Water Park/Gone Fishing/The Water Goes 'Round/Caillou's Test Drive/A Very Good Swimmer!
removed.description: Caillou learns that the best fun is made up and not bought and paid for./Caillou learns about patience when he goes fishing with Daddy and Grandpa at the pier./Grandma is watching Caillou for the day, and he wants her to play trucks with him./When their car breaks down, the family goes shopping for a new one./Caillou gets an introduction to what it means to be handicapped, when, at the pool, he meets Tammy.

removed.title: No Power, No Problem!
removed.description: When the power goes out all over Sodor, Thomas and Friends must use brain-power to navigate the island in creative new ways.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Hide and Sneak
removed.description: Dibble is chosen as "It" in a Whiffle game of Hide-and-Seek. The game turns serious when Bluster traps the Bears inside the Cloudseeker. Dibble and Cheer must find the Whiffles and free her friends.

removed.title: Boo
removed.description: Coco shows Bing how to do really big boos, but what will happen when Bing wants to practice on Charlie?

removed.title: Where's Gilbert?/Where I Saw it Last/Lost in the Jungle
removed.description: Gilbert has gone missing and Caillou is very concerned./Caillou realizes that he has misplaced his new toy car./Caillou learns all about the jungle at playschool.

removed.title: Share Your Care
removed.description: Dibble plants the seeds of a strange bush outside of its natural environment, unaware that she has unleashed a disaster: The plant multiplies and begins to quickly spread. The Bears must find a way to stop its greedy growth before it crowds out all the other plants in the Silver Lining.

removed.title: Caillou's Horn/The Mighty Oak/Get Well Mr. Hinkle/The Big Boat
removed.description: When Sarah gives Caillou an old toy horn, Caillou wants to blow it everywhere./When Mr. Hinkle has a tree cut down, Caillou is afraid his swing tree is next!/When Caillou dresses up like a mailman to deliver Mr. Hinkle's misdirected mail, he finds out Mr. Hinkle is sick./Caillou and family go on a trip on Helen's boat, an old friend of Mom's.

removed.title: All Washed Up
removed.description: Taz decides he doesn't like taking a bath.

removed.title: The Show Must Go On
removed.description: Mushpie loves to sing. The only problem is she is terrible at it! But Lilit, who has never heard her sing before, wants to make Mushpie happy and organizes a concert for her to sing in front of all the other Mushables… who are terrified at the idea! But Lilit doesn't have the heart to admit this to Mushpie.

removed.title: Where I Live/A Good Friend/Just Like Me/Just In Time/Mr. Fixit
removed.description: When an invitation for Clementine's party accidentally ends up at Sarah's, Caillou learns the differences between the addresses of the two homes./When Leo forgets his brand new toy dinosaur in the park, Daddy and Caillou go looking for it./When Clementine tells Caillou how much she likes her older brother, Billy, to teach her things, Caillou sets out to teach something to Rosie./When Caillou's dawdling causes he, Mom and Rosie to be late going to the park, they end up missing Leo./When the washing machine needs fixing, Caillou ends up helping Bob the repairman.

removed.title: Kite
removed.description: Bing and Flop are in the park to fly Bing's Hoppity Voosh kite, and Bing is excited to fly it all by himself. Will Bing be able to?

removed.title: Too Hot to Handle
removed.description: Findley can't resist some freshly baked cookies that are too hot to eat.
